                        </cit>; ter legitur in libro Jobi: <foreign xml:lang="gez">መሐወኒ፡ እንተ፡ ኵለሄ፡ ወእለህስ፡</foreign> <foreign xml:lang="grc">διέσπασέ με κύκλῳ καὶ ᾠχόμην</foreign> 19,10; <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወይልህስ፡</foreign> (v. <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወይፈልስ፡</foreign>) <foreign xml:lang="gez">እምነ፡ ምንባሩ፡</foreign> <foreign xml:lang="grc">καὶ λικμήσει αὐτὸν ἐκ τοῦ τόπου αὐτοῦ</foreign> 27,21; <foreign xml:lang="gez">ትፍሕቅ፡ ነፍስየ፡ ወትልህስ፡</foreign> <foreign xml:lang="grc">ᾤχετό μου ἡ ἐλπὶς ὥσπερ πνεῦμα</foreign> 30,15. – <lbl expand="Vocabularium Aethiopicum, -a -a">Voc. Ae.</lbl>: <foreign xml:lang="gez">እፈልስ፡ እልህስ፡ ዘ፡ እሰድዳለሁ፡</foreign> [In caeteris linguis deest haec eadem radix; cum <foreign xml:lang="gez">ለ</foreign> et <foreign xml:lang="gez">ነ</foreign> saepius permutentur, an comparare licuerit <foreign xml:lang="he">נוּס</foreign> <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la">
                            <quote> aufugere? </quote>
